org.mindswap.owls.grounding
Interface AtomicGrounding<T>

All Superinterfaces:
OWLEntity, OWLIndividual, OWLObject, OWLValue
All Known Subinterfaces:
JavaAtomicGrounding, UPnPAtomicGrounding, WSDLAtomicGrounding
All Known Implementing Classes:
AtomicGroundingImpl, JavaAtomicGroundingImpl, MessageMapAtomicGroundingImpl, UPnPAtomicGroundingImpl, WSDLAtomicGroundingImpl
public interface AtomicGrounding<T>
extends OWLIndividual

Represents a grounding for atomic processes. This interface is intended to be the base for various grounding types such as WSDLAtomicGrounding and UPnPAtomicGrounding classes.

As of OWL-S 1.2 the corresponding concept in the OWL-S grounding ontology is AtomicProcessGrounding.

getDescriptionURL

java.net.URL getDescriptionURL()
Get a URL that describes the properties of this grounding. The nature of the file depends on the actual grounding type, e.g., WSDL grounding will return the URL of the WSDL document, whereas the UPNP grounding returns the UPnP presentation URL.

Returns:
The URL of the document further describing this atomic process grounding.
Throws:
java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - If this grounding does not support this property.

invoke

java.util.concurrent.Future<ValueMap<Output,OWLValue>> invoke(ValueMap<Input,OWLValue> values)
Invoke this grounding with the given input values.

This method is supposed to return immediately for groundings providing asynchronous invocation. For groundings providing synchronous invocation this method may or may not return immediately (a subsequent get on the Future returned is required anyway).

Parameters:
values - Values bound to the input parameters of the backing process.
Returns:
Future representing pending completion of the invocation. The Future's get method will return the values bound to output parameters of the backing atomic process (i.e. the outputs produced by the process) upon successful completion. Otherwise, an ExecutionException is thrown which possibly wraps a causing exception.

invoke

java.util.concurrent.Future<ValueMap<Output,OWLValue>> invoke(ValueMap<Input,OWLValue> values,
                                                              OWLKnowledgeBase kb)
Invoke this grounding with the given input values and use the given KB to store the output values.

This method is supposed to return immediately for groundings providing asynchronous invocation. For groundings providing synchronous invocation this method may or may not return immediately (a subsequent get on the Future returned is required anyway).

Parameters:
values - Values bound to the input parameters of the backing process.
kb - The execution environment to which output values will be added.
Returns:
Future representing pending completion of the invocation. The Future's get method will return the values bound to output parameters of the backing atomic process (i.e. the outputs produced by the process) upon successful completion. Otherwise, an ExecutionException is thrown which possibly wraps a causing exception.

getGrounding

Grounding<? extends AtomicGrounding<T>,T> getGrounding()
Get the enclosing grounding this atomic process grounding belongs to. If it is referenced by more than one grounding pick one arbitrarily.

In OWL-S every atomic process grounding is enclosed by an instance of the concept OWLS.Grounding#Grounding.

Returns:
The enclosing grounding.

getGroundingType

java.lang.String getGroundingType()
Returns the type of grounding such as WSDL or Java, see public constants declared by this interface.

Returns:
A unique name representing the type of this atomic process grounding.
